Politicians inciting violence in Nyanza during nominations and elections will be arrested and no chaos will be tolerated, Nyanza regional coordinator Wilson Njenga said yesterday.He said police are already investigating the chaos witnessed in the April 3 ODM rally in Migori.Politicians who attended the rally have recorded statements with the police, Njenga said.&ldquo;We want to assure you that legal action will be taken against those found to have been involved in the Migori chaos," he added.Njenga and Nyanza regional police coordinator Willy Lugusa assured residents of security during polls.Lugusa cautioned politicians against hiring goons to disrupt peace.&ldquo;We want to make sure that residents within the region go about their daily business uninterrupted,&rdquo; he said Lugusa.